						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar (No. 3) kept near the <hi rend="italic">navagrahas</hi> of the Bālabrahmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Trailōkyamalla [Sōmēśvara I] 1062 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers to the rule of Chālukya Trailōkyamalladēva and seems to register a grant to a deity (name lost).</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 984 Shubhakrātu, Mārgasira, śu, rest of the information is lost. It may be equated with 1062 A.D., November.</p>						

						</summary>
